# Frontend Engineering Rules

## Component Architecture
- Use **functional components** with hooks ONLY — no class components ever
- One component per file — filename matches the exported component name
- Keep components under 200 lines; extract sub-components if larger
- Co-locate component-specific styles, tests, and hooks in the same folder
- Example structure:
  ```
  components/CommandBar/
    index.jsx          ← public export
    CommandBar.jsx     ← implementation
    CommandBar.test.jsx
    useCommandBar.js   ← local hook
  ```

## State Management
- **Local state** → `useState` / `useReducer`
- **Global state** → Zustand stores in `src/store/`
- **Server state** → direct service calls + local loading/error state in hooks
- NEVER put API call logic inside a component body — use `src/services/`
- NEVER use `localStorage` for JWTs — use `sessionStorage` or Electron secure storage

## Naming Conventions
- Components: `PascalCase` (e.g., `CommandBar`, `AuthPage`)
- Hooks: `camelCase` prefixed with `use` (e.g., `useCommand`, `useAuthStore`)
- Services: `camelCase` + `Service` suffix (e.g., `authService`, `commandService`)
- Constants: `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE`
- CSS classes: `kebab-case`

## Code Quality
- All exported functions must have JSDoc comments
- No `console.log` in production code — use `console.warn` / `console.error` only
- Prefer named exports over default exports for components
- Run `npm run lint` before every commit (enforced by Husky)
- All new components need a corresponding `.test.jsx` file

## API Calls
- ALL API calls go through `src/services/apiClient.js` (Axios instance with JWT interceptors)
- Handle loading/error states explicitly in every async operation
- Never expose raw Axios errors to the UI — map to user-friendly messages

## IPC (Electron)
- Renderer process NEVER uses Node.js directly
- All main-process calls go through `window.slashAI.*` (contextBridge)
- Only whitelisted channels in `preload.js` are allowed
- Add new channels to BOTH the whitelist AND `ipc/` handler file

## Performance
- Lazy-load page components with `React.lazy` + `Suspense`
- Memoize expensive computations with `useMemo`
- Stable callback references with `useCallback` where passed as props
- Virtualize lists over 50 items (use `react-virtual` or similar)
